cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SI 

The paper deals with randomized linear algebra algorithms, which are often used in numerical analysis and scientific computing. Therefore, cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is the most likely category. The paper also involves matrix operations and low-rank matrix approximation, which are relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of randomized algorithms and the analysis of their efficacy also falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
